<subSubSection id="C37B9DF9FFA1FF898FC44B37FB0BA168" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BDECE72FFA1FF898FC44B37FEEFA063" blockId="13.[189,303,1036,1062]" box="[189,303,1036,1062]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<heading id="D096791EFFA1FF898FC44B37FEEFA063" bold="true" box="[189,303,1036,1062]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA1FF898FC44B37FEEFA063" bold="true" box="[189,303,1036,1062]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDECE72FFA1FF898FC44B00FB0BA168" blockId="13.[189,1399,1083,1325]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
The species was described from a laboratory strain collected from the Tsimbazaza Botanical Park in Antananarivo in 1980. With Jean R. David and Vincent Debat, we collected it in 
<date id="FFDFE8B2FFA1FF898BFD4B64FAF5A03C" box="[1156,1333,1119,1145]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2008" valueMax="2010">2008 and 2010</date>
from Andasibe, Mandraka and Ranomafana. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF0B383FFA1FF898DE94BB8FCF3A0D8" author="Rafael V." box="[656,819,1155,1181]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe zoologique de France" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="179 - 189" part="109" refId="ref12862" refString="Rafael V. 1984. Relations interspecifiques dans le nouveau complexe africain de Drosophila bakoue du groupe melanogaster, sous-groupe montium (Diptera, Drosophilidae). Bulletin de la Societe zoologique de France 109: 179 - 189." title="Relations interspecifiques dans le nouveau complexe africain de Drosophila bakoue du groupe melanogaster, sous-groupe montium (Diptera, Drosophilidae)" type="journal article" year="1984">Rafael (1984)</bibRefCitation>
showed that 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFA1FF898CA84BBFFB41A0D8" authorityName="Tsacas &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="1982" box="[977,1153,1155,1181]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malagassya">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA1FF898CA84BBFFB41A0D8" box="[977,1153,1155,1181]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">D. malagassya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
crossed readily with a Cameroonian strain attributed to 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFA1FF898D244B9CFD17A084" authorityName="Tsacas &amp; Lachaise" authorityYear="1974" box="[605,727,1191,1217]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bakoue">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA1FF898D244B9CFD17A084" box="[605,727,1191,1217]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">D. bakoue</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, producing sterile F 
<specimenCount id="9D6705FBFFA1FF898CB24B9CFBE3A085" box="[971,1059,1190,1217]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="male">1 males</specimenCount>
and females, and to a lesser degree with 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFA1FF898E344BF0FE02A0A1" authorityName="Bock &amp; Wheeler" authorityYear="1972" box="[333,450,1227,1252]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tsacasi">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA1FF898E344BF0FE02A0A1" box="[333,450,1227,1252]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">D. tsacasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, producing a few or unviable F1 flies. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF0B383FFA1FF898CFC4BF1FBA3A0A1" author="David J. R. &amp; Yassin A. &amp; Gidaszewski N. &amp; Debat V." box="[901,1123,1226,1252]" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe entomologique de France" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="336 - 342" part="50" refId="ref12333" refString="David J. R., Yassin A., Gidaszewski N. &amp; Debat V. 2014. Drosophilids (Diptera) from Mayotte island: an annotated list of species collected in 2013 and comments on the colonisation of Indian Ocean Islands. Annales de la Societe entomologique de France 50: 336 - 342. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00379271.2014.938548" title="Drosophilids (Diptera) from Mayotte island: an annotated list of species collected in 2013 and comments on the colonisation of Indian Ocean Islands" type="journal article" year="2014">
David 
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA1FF898CAD4BF0FBCEA0A1" box="[980,1038,1226,1252]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">et al.</emphasis>
(2014)
</bibRefCitation>
suggested the presence of 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFA1FF898FA44BD4FE4CA14D" authorityName="Tsacas &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="1982" box="[221,396,1262,1288]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malagassya">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA1FF898FA44BD4FE4CA14D" box="[221,396,1262,1288]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">D. malagassya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the island of 
<collectingCountry id="F3768EE2FFA1FF898D294BD4FD72A14C" box="[592,690,1263,1289]" name="Mayotte" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Mayotte</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry id="F3768EE2FFA1FF898DB84BD5FCEEA14D" box="[705,814,1262,1288]" name="Comoros" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Comoros</collectingCountry>
archipelago), but the 
<collectingCountry id="F3768EE2FFA1FF898B564BD4FB51A14C" box="[1071,1169,1263,1289]" name="Mayotte" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Mayotte</collectingCountry>
strain turned out to be 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFA1FF898F994A28FE8FA169" box="[224,335,1299,1324]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seguyi">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA1FF898F994A28FE8FA169" box="[224,335,1299,1324]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">D. seguyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFA1FF898D6D4A28FD03A169" authorityName="Tsacas &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="1982" box="[532,707,1298,1324]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malagassya">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA1FF898D6D4A28FD03A169" box="[532,707,1298,1324]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">D. malagassya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have two color morphs (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF0B383FFA1FF898C9E4A29FB7FA168" author="Yassin A. &amp; Delaney E. K. &amp; Reddiex A. J. &amp; Seher T. D. &amp; Bastide H. &amp; Appleton N. C. &amp; Lack J. B. &amp; David J. R. &amp; Chenoweth S. F. &amp; Pool J. E. &amp; Kopp A." box="[999,1215,1298,1325]" journalOrPublisher="Current Biology" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="2412 - 2422" part="26" refId="ref13717" refString="Yassin A., Delaney E. K., Reddiex A. J., Seher T. D., Bastide H., Appleton N. C., Lack J. B., David J. R., Chenoweth S. F., Pool J. E. &amp; Kopp A. 2016. The pdm 3 locus is a hotspot for recurrent evolution of female-limited color dimorphism in Drosophila. Current Biology 26: 2412 - 2422. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. cub. 2016.07.016" title="The pdm 3 locus is a hotspot for recurrent evolution of female-limited color dimorphism in Drosophila" type="journal article" year="2016">
Yassin 
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA1FF898B444A28FBB8A169" box="[1085,1144,1298,1324]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
